sdp/logs/Verify_T-021_20260416T043834Z_1776337553.log:3884:./sdp/logs/Verify_T-006_20260416T043834Z_1776330893.log:1969:sdp/logs/Verify_T-020_20260416T043834Z_1776326247.log:4527:- If federated and standalone startup are both supported, pass an explicit mode into `bootstrap_identity()` when entering those startup flows; keep the recurring hardening check for identity persistence between boots.
sdp/logs/Verify_T-021_20260416T043834Z_1776337553.log:3885:./sdp/logs/Verify_T-006_20260416T043834Z_1776330893.log:1970:sdp/logs/Verify_T-020_20260416T043834Z_1776326247.log:4544:- Minor: `bootstrap_identity()` in startup is invoked before `FirstBootAnnouncer` but without explicit mode, so a first-run federated bootstrap can default to standalone unless identity already exists.
